I '''Deepak Chopra''' ({{lang-hi|दीपक  चोपड़ा}}; mibait Octubre 22, 1946) metung yang Americanung talapanulu ampong talasulat a mibait [[India]].  Tinuru ya i Chopra kareng eskuelang medikal ning [[Tufts University]], [[Boston University]] ampong [[Harvard University]]. Megi yang Chief of Staff ning [[New England Memorial Hospital]] (NEMH) king [[Massachusetts]],<ref name=Woop/> bayu ya minta king pribadung pamanulu (''private practice'').<ref name=Woop/> Anyang 1985, mikit ya i Chopra ampo i [[Maharishi Mahesh Yogi]], at inagkat ne i Choprang manigaral king [[Ayurveda]].<ref name="webindia"/><ref name="novamagazine.com.au">{{cite web | first=Rosamund | last=Burton | title=Peace Seeker | url=http://www.novamagazine.com.au/article_archive/06_04_Peace%20seeker.htm | work= Nova Magazine | accessdate = 2008-11-30 }}</ref> Likwan neng Chopra ing pusisyun na king NEMH at megi yang a pamuntuk ning [[American Association of Ayurvedic Medicine]], at kaybat medical director ning [[Maharishi Vedic Approach to Health|Maharishi Ayurveda]] Health Center.<ref name="webindia"/><ref name="novamagazine.com.au"/><ref name=Daniel>{{cite web | last=Redwood | first=Daniel DC | url=http://www.healthy.net/scr/interview.asp?Id=167 | title = Quantum Healing | work=HealthWorld Online | accessdate=2008-11-30 }}</ref> 

Kanitang 1996, tetag neng Chopra ampo ing neurologist a i David Simon ing Chopra Center for Wellbeing, nung nu makayanib ing Ayurveda king kayang kaparalanan, at atyu king [[La Jolla, California]]. Babye lang kreditu para king taglus-taglus a pamagaral king pamanulu (''continuing medical education'') deng [[University of California, San Diego]], School of Medicine ampong [[American Medical Association]] para kareng aliwang programang yampang da kareng talapanulu (''physicians'') king Chopra Center.<ref name=Woop/><ref name="webindia"/><ref name="novamagazine.com.au"/> Anyang 2002, inalis neng Chopra ampong Simon ing the Chopra Center king lugal ning [[La Costa Resort and Spa]] king [[Carlsbad, California]]. Kanitang 2009, tetag neng Chopra ing [[Chopra Foundation]] ba yang isulung ing pangimut ning pamanulung pangkaisipan ampong pangkatawan, pamagaral, ampong pamanyalugsug to advance the cause of mind/body spiritual healing, education, and (''research'') kapamilatan ning pamangalap pondu para kareng mepiling proyektu.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deepakchopra.com/chopra-foundation/about/ |title=Sages and Scientists Symposium |publisher=Deepak Chopra |date= |accessdate=2011-02-18}}</ref>

Mekasulat neng maygit 65 books a libru i Chopra, at 19 la reng ''[[New York Times]]'' bestseller. Milikas no kareng 35 a amanu deng kayang libru, at maygit nong 20 milyun deng misali king mabilug a yatu.<ref name="World Wellness"/> Tinanggap neng dakal a galal i Chopra, kayabe ya ing Oceana Award (2009),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://na.oceana.org/en/news-media/press-center/press-releases/deepak-chopra-and-arianna-huffington-to-be-honored-at-oceana-s-2009-partners-award-gala |title=Deepak Chopra and Arianna Huffington to be Honored at Oceana’s 2009 Partners Award Gala | publisher= Oceana | date= 2009-10-28 |accessdate= 2011-02-18}}</ref> ing [[Cinequest]] Life of a Maverick Award (2010),<ref name= BizWire>{{Citation | newspaper = Business Wire | title = Chopra Receives the Life of Maverick Award at Cinequest 2010 | date = February 2, 2010 | url = http://www.businesswire.com/portal/site/home/permalink/?ndmViewId=news_view&newsId=20100202005787&newsLang=en}}.</ref> Humanitarian Starlite Award (2010),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thestarlitegala.com/2010/deepak-en.php |title=2010 Humanitarian Starlite Award – Deepak Chopra |publisher=The star lite gala |date= 2000-03-21 |accessdate= 2011-02-18}}</ref> and the GOI Peace Award (2010).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goipeace.or.jp/english/activities/award/award2010.html |title=Deepak Chopra Receives the 2010 Goi Peace Award |publisher= Goi peace | place = [[Japan | JP]] |date = 2010-11-07 | accessdate = 2011-02-18}}</ref> Agpang kareng aliwa, ya ing "metung ya kareng manimunang pekapun ning pangimut a kaisipan-katawan-espiritu" ("He is thought by some to be "one of the pre-eminent leaders of the mind-body-spirit movement").<ref name =BizWire/>

